WEBVTT

00:02.370 --> 00:03.737
-The Lyons are
hitting back on Empire.
-(shouts)

00:03.771 --> 00:06.174
-May we rise.
-Like we always do.

00:06.207 --> 00:08.076
Catch all-new episodes
Wednesdays.

00:08.109 --> 00:10.211
And check out
our other Fox programs--

00:10.244 --> 00:13.081
Star, 9-1-1, and The Resident.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.215
That's a win-win.

00:14.248 --> 00:15.749
Only on Fox.

00:17.118 --> 00:19.153
-Previously on Empire...
-I'm Damon Cross.

00:19.187 --> 00:20.821
I'm a game changer.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.123
Your boy sold the Derrick Adams.

00:22.156 --> 00:24.725
-Get me that damn painting.
-TIANA: Walking around with

00:24.758 --> 00:27.895
that gun on your hip is not
gonna bring back what we lost.

00:27.928 --> 00:30.264
You're a tech guy,
so why Empire?

00:30.298 --> 00:32.900
I'm going to erase him
from the face of the earth.

00:32.933 --> 00:34.868
How's that for talent, Dad?

00:34.902 --> 00:36.904
He doesn't love you, Maya.
That's not love.

00:36.937 --> 00:38.539
Cookie, you have your own family
to fix.

00:38.572 --> 00:39.873
I got a loft in SoHo.

00:39.907 --> 00:42.376
You promised that
you would never tell or sell.

00:42.410 --> 00:44.512
CANDACE: You called the police
on my son.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.214
I never want to see you again.

00:56.890 --> 00:59.760
Lucious, I just got a call
that he's in surgery.

00:59.793 --> 01:03.597
What happened?
Is that blood?

01:03.631 --> 01:05.266
Lucious, what did you do?

01:07.801 --> 01:10.271
What did you do?

01:10.304 --> 01:12.306
*

01:17.245 --> 01:18.579
COOKIE (sighs):
Come on, Candace.

01:18.612 --> 01:20.114
Stop being like this.

01:20.148 --> 01:21.882
We need to talk this through.

01:21.915 --> 01:24.152
Can you call me back, please?

01:24.185 --> 01:26.287
You need to stop being
like this.

01:26.320 --> 01:28.322
You know how your sister is,
baby.

01:28.356 --> 01:30.324
It's been two weeks, Lucious.

01:30.358 --> 01:33.294
I need to know how she's doing,
how's Franklin doing.

01:33.327 --> 01:36.897
(groans) She's gonna talk
when she's good and ready, baby.

01:36.930 --> 01:38.799
Maybe I shouldn't have
called the cops.

01:38.832 --> 01:40.334
Come on, now.

01:40.368 --> 01:42.136
Baby, you have

01:42.170 --> 01:45.639
been through this...
a dozen times.

01:45.673 --> 01:47.741
Stop beating yourself up
over this.

01:47.775 --> 01:49.910
You did the right thing.

01:49.943 --> 01:52.513
Besides, not like
she's the only one

01:52.546 --> 01:54.415
that's been through the fire,
you know?

01:54.448 --> 01:56.284
We done been...
Oh, man.

01:56.317 --> 01:58.352
We forgot Jamal.

01:58.386 --> 02:00.654
-This morning.
-Aah. What time is it? (sighs)

02:02.790 --> 02:04.792
* You feel like a vacation

02:04.825 --> 02:07.261
* You feel
like a vacation *

02:07.295 --> 02:09.463
-* 'Cause loving you is easy
-(sighs)

02:09.497 --> 02:11.765
* Like a summer day

02:11.799 --> 02:14.502
* Fun without the games

02:14.535 --> 02:17.104
* You're good for me,
oh, baby *

02:17.137 --> 02:18.539
* Loving you is easy

02:18.572 --> 02:21.175
* We do it every night

02:21.209 --> 02:24.178
* It's like paradise

02:24.212 --> 02:27.681
* Just you and I, oh, baby.

02:27.715 --> 02:29.217
Thank you.

02:31.319 --> 02:33.354
Jamal, the new song is fire.

02:33.387 --> 02:35.189
Thank you, man.
I saw you jamming.

02:35.223 --> 02:37.225
-Y'all know y'all saw that.
-No, I-I was in it. Um,

02:37.258 --> 02:38.826
it seems like
you're in a really good place.

02:38.859 --> 02:40.628
Oh, definitely.
Amazing place. Um...

02:40.661 --> 02:42.463
-Yeah. No. The Lyons are back.
-Mm.

02:42.496 --> 02:44.565
-You know? And, uh,
with my family...
-Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

02:44.598 --> 02:47.034
...my mom and dad starting
the new Lyon Family Management,

02:47.067 --> 02:48.702
and we're about
to do this crazy showcase.

02:48.736 --> 02:51.205
-Oh, you'll be performing?
-Of cour... of course, man.

02:51.239 --> 02:52.706
-Come on. Me and...
-Okay. All right, okay.

02:52.740 --> 02:55.376
...my brother, Hakeem, you know,
we'll be releasing new music.

02:55.409 --> 02:57.711
And then, also, on top of that,
the brand-new artists...

02:57.745 --> 03:00.514
-Mm.
-...who are just amazing,
at Lyon Family Management.

03:00.548 --> 03:02.483
So, yes, LFM is ready

03:02.516 --> 03:05.152
for a second time around
to crush the music industry.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.054
-All right, we cannot wait.
-(Cookie sighs)

03:07.087 --> 03:09.423
KEVIN: By the way, you seem like
you're really happy. What's up?

03:09.457 --> 03:10.724
-I'm so happy.
I'm so happy, man.
-What's up?

03:10.758 --> 03:12.426
I'm so happy.
I'm happy to be home.

03:12.460 --> 03:14.061
I'm happy to, you know...

03:14.094 --> 03:16.730
I'm in love,
I'm, uh, I'm-I'm engaged.

03:16.764 --> 03:18.699
I'm very happy.

03:18.732 --> 03:21.702
-Yeah, yeah. Yeah.
-Congratulations.

03:21.735 --> 03:23.371
You heard it here first.
Jamal Lyon engaged.

03:23.404 --> 03:25.105
Who's the lucky guy?

03:25.138 --> 03:26.574
Uh, his name is Kai Givens.

03:26.607 --> 03:28.342
-Kai. I know Kai.
-You do.

03:28.376 --> 03:31.345
-Kai Givens is
a great TV journalist. Yeah.
-Yeah.

03:31.379 --> 03:34.415
-Please give him
my best regards.
-Absolutely. Uh, babe?

03:34.448 --> 03:36.116
Uh... (chuckles)
Best regards.

03:36.149 --> 03:38.018
He's right there. Hey, babe.

03:38.051 --> 03:42.089
Oh, Kai. Trevor, let's get
this shot. Hey, Kai. Kai.

03:42.122 --> 03:44.057
How long have you
and Jamal been an item?

03:44.091 --> 03:45.526
How did you meet?

03:45.559 --> 03:47.027
Don't that make you feel better?

03:47.060 --> 03:48.596
(laughing):
Uh, yes!

03:48.629 --> 03:50.598
Jamal's got the public
all primed for the showcase.

03:50.631 --> 03:52.099
I'm going to work.

03:52.132 --> 03:53.601
Oh, will you do me a favor
and get me

03:53.634 --> 03:55.636
something out of the top drawer?
I left it in there.

03:55.669 --> 03:58.071
-What...?
-I got you something.

03:58.105 --> 04:00.441
Um, Lucious,
we are still busted.

04:01.509 --> 04:03.043
Open the box.

04:03.076 --> 04:04.578
What is this?

04:04.612 --> 04:06.380
(Lucious sighs)

04:06.414 --> 04:08.716
(chuckling):
What is this?

04:08.749 --> 04:11.251
This is your favorite
jewelry store,

04:11.285 --> 04:13.621
and it's a picture
of all the things you want,

04:13.654 --> 04:15.723
and I'm-a buy everything
in that window

04:15.756 --> 04:17.958
-because you're my everything.
-(chuckling)

04:17.991 --> 04:20.628
And I'm all in, baby.

04:20.661 --> 04:24.264
-You're so sweet. (chuckling)
-Mmm.

04:24.298 --> 04:26.300
I'm telling you, if you peek,
I'm gonna come back

04:26.334 --> 04:28.469
-in your next life...
-Don't you run me into a wall.

04:28.502 --> 04:30.638
-No. Turn, turn, turn!
-No! Stop!

04:30.671 --> 04:32.139
(both laughing)

04:32.172 --> 04:33.641
-Five more steps.
-Ooh, my earring fell.

04:33.674 --> 04:37.110
One, two, three, four, five.

04:37.144 --> 04:38.646
-Here.
-Okay, can I open my eyes?

04:38.679 --> 04:40.648
-Okay! Yeah, wait.
On three. One, two...
-Three!

04:40.681 --> 04:42.683
-Three.
-(Cookie gasps loudly)

04:42.716 --> 04:45.486
-God, is that a Derrick Adams?
-(chuckling)

04:47.154 --> 04:50.591
Oh, Lucious, it's amazing!

04:50.624 --> 04:52.626
But we can't afford this.

04:52.660 --> 04:57.030
This portrait is my bet on us.

04:57.064 --> 04:59.367
It's you and me forever, kid.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.268
Forever.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.472
(chuckling)
You are so sweet.

05:06.239 --> 05:08.609
-You just let that stuff go,
okay?
-Mmm.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.644
-Okay.
-You did the right thing.

05:13.180 --> 05:15.315
*

05:17.385 --> 05:20.187
Thanks for gathering
on short notice, everyone.

05:20.220 --> 05:22.956
I wanted you to hear this from
me before it hits the press.

05:22.990 --> 05:25.225
Effective immediately,

05:25.258 --> 05:27.495
Empire is pulling
Lucious Lyon's music

05:27.528 --> 05:29.062
from all streaming platforms,

05:29.096 --> 05:30.664
store shelves
and ancillary markets.

05:30.698 --> 05:34.167
That includes film,
television and commercials.

05:34.201 --> 05:35.503
I'm sorry. I thought

05:35.536 --> 05:37.538
that you and Lucious
had kissed and made up.

05:37.571 --> 05:40.340
You of all people should know
that this is just business.

05:40.374 --> 05:43.310
Just business?! I'm sorry.
What is the goal here?

05:43.343 --> 05:46.514
Years ago, Disney Animation
proved, very convincingly,

05:46.547 --> 05:49.049
that temporary scarcity leads
to increased demand

05:49.082 --> 05:51.218
and inevitably,
to windfall profits.

05:51.251 --> 05:55.222
True, but they warned their fans
first before they vaulted,

05:55.255 --> 05:56.890
so people ran out
and bought a bunch of product.

05:56.924 --> 05:58.225
I did.

05:58.258 --> 06:01.228
You have kids, right, Lavar?

06:01.261 --> 06:03.063
A little boy and a girl,
eight and ten.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.231
I bet they love Disney,
don't they?

06:04.264 --> 06:06.099
(chuckling):
Absolute fanatics.

06:06.133 --> 06:08.101
As a matter of fact, I'm taking
'em over spring break.

06:08.135 --> 06:09.369
-Oh, that's fantastic.
-Oh.

06:09.403 --> 06:10.904
I bet
that's a rather expensive trip

06:10.938 --> 06:12.272
when you're on unemployment.

06:13.541 --> 06:16.944
-You're fired.
-I'm sorry, what? What did I do?

06:16.977 --> 06:18.879
You spoke when you should have
been listening.

06:19.913 --> 06:21.615
Meeting adjourned.

